    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-3">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How long does an SEO audit take?</summary>
        <p>A comprehensive SEO audit for a Guildford business takes 5 to 10 working days depending on site size. A 50-page professional services site takes around 5 days. E-commerce or property listing sites with thousands of pages require up to 10 days for thorough analysis.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What is the difference between a free and paid SEO audit?</summary>
        <p>A free SEO audit provides a high-level summary of your site's main issues using automated tools. A paid audit includes manual expert analysis, server log review, competitor benchmarking, content gap analysis, and a prioritised action plan with implementation guidance. The paid audit is what actually drives ranking improvements.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do I need an SEO audit if my site is already ranking?</summary>
        <p>Yes. Sites that rank well today often have hidden technical debt that makes them vulnerable to algorithm updates. An audit identifies risks before they become ranking losses. It also uncovers missed opportunities: pages that could rank higher, keywords you are not targeting, and local search features you are not leveraging.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Will you implement the audit recommendations?</summary>
        <p>The audit is a standalone deliverable. Implementation is available as a separate engagement. Many Guildford businesses commission the audit first, review the findings, and then engage us for implementation. Alternatively, your in-house team or developers can implement using our detailed specifications.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How often should a Guildford business get an SEO audit?</summary>
        <p>We recommend a comprehensive audit annually, with quarterly technical health checks in between. If your site undergoes a major redesign, CMS migration, or experiences a sudden ranking drop, an immediate audit is warranted regardless of schedule.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What tools do you use for the audit?</summary>
        <p>We use a combination of professional crawling tools, Google Search Console data, server log analysis, Core Web Vitals testing (both lab and field data), structured data validators, and manual review. No single tool catches everything, which is why our audits combine automated scanning with expert analysis.</p>
      </details>
    </div>

